WEBVTT

00:01.275 --> 00:04.182
<i>PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i>ON "WAYWARD PINES"...</i>

00:04.182 --> 00:06.554
YOU DIDN'T THINK WAYWARD PINES
RAN ITSELF, DID YOU?

00:08.726 --> 00:11.600
HEY. WHO ARE
ALL OF THESE PEOPLE?

00:11.600 --> 00:13.204
VOLUNTEERS.

00:13.204 --> 00:14.774
WE WERE CHANGING THE WORLD,
AND, AS A RESULT...

00:14.774 --> 00:16.378
[ SCREECHING ]
OH!

00:16.378 --> 00:18.450
...WE, OURSELVES,
WERE BEGINNING TO CHANGE.

00:21.224 --> 00:24.464
TESTING CRYONIC SUSPENSION WAS
BOTH DANGEROUS AND ILLEGAL.

00:24.464 --> 00:26.469
THEY'RE ALL ASLEEP.
YES.

00:26.469 --> 00:28.608
THIS ISN'T A LITTLE TOWN,
ETHAN.

00:28.608 --> 00:29.811
THIS IS
A NEW CIVILIZATION.

00:29.811 --> 00:31.348
YOU HAVE TO
TELL THEM THE TRUTH.

00:31.348 --> 00:32.751
PEOPLE ARE FRAGILE.

00:32.751 --> 00:34.689
THEY NEED TIME TO ADAPT.

00:34.689 --> 00:37.329
YOUNG MINDS ARE FEARLESS.

00:37.329 --> 00:39.000
WELCOME
TO THE FIRST GENERATION.

00:39.000 --> 00:40.738
THEY'RE LESS INGRAINED
IN THE OLD WORLD.

00:40.738 --> 00:42.743
THEY CAN ACCEPT THE TRUTH.

00:42.743 --> 00:43.979
THERE'S A NEW THREAT.

00:43.979 --> 00:45.884
WE DON'T KNOW
WHO THEY ARE,

00:45.884 --> 00:48.490
BUT THEY'RE GONNA TAKE DOWN
THE FENCE.

00:48.490 --> 00:49.660
IF THEY SUCCEED --

00:49.660 --> 00:51.363
THEY'RE NOT
GOING TO SUCCEED.

00:51.363 --> 00:52.500
[ CRANKING ]

00:52.500 --> 00:53.503
[ <i>SOFT MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

00:53.503 --> 00:55.508
IT'S READY.

00:57.847 --> 01:00.453
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

01:00.453 --> 01:02.324
Pilcher: ETHAN.

01:02.324 --> 01:04.563
IT IS IMPERATIVE
YOU TELL NO ONE ABOUT

01:04.563 --> 01:07.537
WHAT YOU'VE SEEN
AND WHAT YOU'VE HEARD.

01:07.537 --> 01:10.277
I BELIEVE
THE SURVIVAL OF HUMANITY

01:10.277 --> 01:12.683
MAY WELL BE
IN OUR HANDS.

01:24.812 --> 01:28.087
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

01:30.527 --> 01:33.401
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

01:35.940 --> 01:38.546
ETHAN.

01:38.546 --> 01:40.418
WHEN DID YOU GET BACK?

01:40.418 --> 01:42.924
HAVE YOU BEEN SITTING HERE
ALL NIGHT?

01:42.924 --> 01:45.029
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU FOUND SOMETHING.

01:45.029 --> 01:46.866
WE HAVE GOT TO GET BACK
TO SEATTLE.

01:46.866 --> 01:48.504
I CANNOT GET AHOLD
OF ANYBODY.

01:48.504 --> 01:50.041
MOM'S SURGERY IS
ON WEDNESDAY.

01:50.041 --> 01:53.650
THERESA, THERESA.

01:53.650 --> 01:56.858
THERE IS NO SEATTLE.

01:58.028 --> 02:00.633
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

02:05.012 --> 02:07.885
LOOK.

02:07.885 --> 02:10.759
WHEN WE WERE PULLED
FROM THOSE CAR WRECKS...

02:12.497 --> 02:16.607
...WE WEREN'T TAKEN
DIRECTLY HERE.

02:16.607 --> 02:19.514
WE WERE PUT INTO
SOME KIND OF A...

02:19.514 --> 02:22.387
SUSPENDED ANIMATION.

02:22.387 --> 02:23.524
[ GROANS ]

02:23.524 --> 02:25.662
WHAT HAPPENED TO
YOUR ARM?

02:25.662 --> 02:28.769
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'RE GONNA THINK I'M CRAZY.

02:28.769 --> 02:30.039
[ SIGHS ]

02:30.039 --> 02:34.149
BUT THERE'S THESE CREATURES
OUT THERE...

02:34.149 --> 02:36.889
MONSTERS.

02:36.889 --> 02:39.897
I SAW THEM
WITH MY OWN EYES.

02:39.897 --> 02:43.171
CITIES DESTROYED.

02:43.171 --> 02:46.045
THIS...

02:46.045 --> 02:49.888
THIS FAKE LITTLE TOWN
IS ALL THAT'S LEFT.

02:51.492 --> 02:54.031
ETHAN, WHAT DID THEY DO
TO YOU?

02:54.031 --> 02:56.036
[ SIGHS ]

02:56.036 --> 02:57.473
WHAT DID THEY DO
TO YOU?

02:57.473 --> 02:58.910
DID THEY TAKE YOU BACK
TO THE HOSPITAL?

02:58.910 --> 03:01.918
NO.

03:01.918 --> 03:03.187
I NEED YOU TO
TRY TO REMEMBER

03:03.187 --> 03:05.092
IF THEY DID
ANYTHING TO YOU,

03:05.092 --> 03:07.698
IF THEY INJECTED YOU
WITH SOMETHING.
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME.

03:07.698 --> 03:09.803
ARE YOU SURE?
I WASN'T AT THE HOSPITAL!

03:16.954 --> 03:18.191
[ SIGHS ] 4,028?

03:18.191 --> 03:20.730
NOW, WHAT -- OKAY,
WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

03:20.730 --> 03:22.735
THAT'S THE DATE.

03:24.472 --> 03:27.146
[ SIGHS ] ETHAN.

03:32.860 --> 03:34.999
[ IGNITION BUZZING ]

03:34.999 --> 03:38.006
[ BEEPING ]

03:38.006 --> 03:39.276
[ BUZZING, BEEPING STOP ]

03:39.276 --> 03:40.980
WHAT'S WRONG?

03:42.651 --> 03:44.188
IT'S THE STARTER.

03:46.761 --> 03:49.033
THIS MIGHT TAKE A WHILE.
YOU GUYS SHOULD WALK.

03:50.738 --> 03:53.110
OKAY.

03:53.110 --> 03:54.948
SURE.

03:54.948 --> 03:56.218
LET'S GO.

03:59.693 --> 04:01.831
OH. SORRY, SORRY.

04:17.837 --> 04:19.709
[ METAL CREAKS ]

04:50.651 --> 04:52.054
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

06:08.943 --> 06:10.781
[ SIGHS ]

06:26.386 --> 06:27.389
[ DOOR OPENS ]

06:27.389 --> 06:30.129
GOOD MORNING,
MR. BURKE.

06:30.129 --> 06:31.297
[ SIGHS ]

06:31.297 --> 06:33.002
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING, PAM?

06:33.002 --> 06:36.511
NO, BUT I THINK I CAN HELP <i>YOU</i>
WITH SOMETHING.

06:36.511 --> 06:38.883
REALLY?

06:38.883 --> 06:42.959
OH. FRANKLIN DOBBS.

06:42.959 --> 06:46.068
DO YOU THINK HE'S INVOLVED
WITH THESE SUBVERSIVES?

06:46.068 --> 06:48.808
I DON'T KNOW.

06:48.808 --> 06:51.213
BUT WHEN I FIND OUT THE ANSWER
TO THAT QUESTION,

06:51.213 --> 06:53.318
YOU'LL BE
THE FIRST TO KNOW.

06:53.318 --> 06:55.056
UNTIL THEN,
I'VE GOT TO DO MY JOB,

06:55.056 --> 06:57.195
SO IF YOU DON'T MIND...

06:57.195 --> 06:59.935
NO, I DON'T MIND.
GO AHEAD. DO YOUR JOB.

06:59.935 --> 07:01.873
I'M JUST HERE TO HELP.

07:01.873 --> 07:04.011
[ SIGHS ]

07:04.011 --> 07:06.250
I WOULD DO ANYTHING
FOR MY BROTHER.

07:06.250 --> 07:09.391
EVEN WORK HAND-IN-HAND
WITH YOU.

07:09.391 --> 07:10.995
SO, HOW ABOUT IT?

07:10.995 --> 07:13.869
YOU CAN'T DO THIS ALONE.
YOU NEED SOME HELP.

07:13.869 --> 07:16.943
I CAN BE
A VERY GOOD FRIEND.

07:20.218 --> 07:23.325
HOW ABOUT GIVING ME ACCESS
TO THE SURVEILLANCE SYSTEM

07:23.325 --> 07:26.333
SO I CAN SEE
WHAT FRANKLIN'S BEEN UP TO?

07:28.271 --> 07:31.880
S-- I KIND OF THOUGHT
WE HAD MOVED PAST

07:31.880 --> 07:35.422
THIS WHOLE
"WALK YOUR KID TO SCHOOL" THING.

07:35.422 --> 07:37.193
[ SNIFFS ]

07:37.193 --> 07:40.034
I JUST WANTED TO SPEND TIME
WITH YOU, IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

07:41.571 --> 07:45.179
EVERYTHING OKAY?

07:45.179 --> 07:47.451
YEAH.

07:47.451 --> 07:50.158
YOU EVER MISS SEATTLE?

07:51.561 --> 07:53.901
I DON'T REALLY THINK
ABOUT IT.

07:53.901 --> 07:55.136
REALLY?

07:55.136 --> 07:58.178
NOT EVEN CAMPING
WITH YOUR COUSINS

07:58.178 --> 07:59.514
OR PLAYING WITH STANLEY?

07:59.514 --> 08:02.421
[ LAUGHS ] STANLEY.

08:02.421 --> 08:05.997
WE'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO
THINK ABOUT THE PAST.

08:05.997 --> 08:07.635
RIGHT.

08:07.635 --> 08:10.007
GOOD MORNING.

08:10.007 --> 08:12.680
GOOD MORNING,
DR. JENKINS.

08:16.289 --> 08:17.492
HEY.

08:17.492 --> 08:20.299
I LIKE IT HERE, MOM.
I HAVE FRIENDS.

08:20.299 --> 08:22.137
I LIKE SCHOOL.

08:22.137 --> 08:23.674
YOU'D PROBABLY LIKE IT,
TOO,

08:23.674 --> 08:26.547
IF YOU GAVE IT
HALF A CHANCE.

08:26.547 --> 08:28.452
OKAY, WELL, I'M GLAD THINGS
ARE WORKING OUT FOR YOU.

08:28.452 --> 08:31.459
GOOD MORNING, GUYS.

08:31.459 --> 08:33.597
NICE TO SEE YOU,
THERESA.

08:33.597 --> 08:34.667
HI.

08:34.667 --> 08:37.006
HEY, BEN.
MRS. BURKE.

08:37.006 --> 08:40.247
AMY, WILL YOU HELP BEN
FIND A BIOLOGY TEXTBOOK?

08:40.247 --> 08:42.286
THERE'S A BIG STACK OF THEM
BEHIND MY DESK.

08:42.286 --> 08:45.226
YEAH, SURE.
COME ON.

08:45.226 --> 08:47.733
YOU KNOW,
I HAVE NOT SET FOOT

08:47.733 --> 08:49.471
INSIDE THAT SCHOOL
OR YOUR CLASSROOM.

08:49.471 --> 08:50.974
IS THERE A TOUR

08:50.974 --> 08:52.177
OR A PARENT/TEACHER
CONFERENCE COMING UP?

08:52.177 --> 08:54.181
SCHOOL IS FOR CHILDREN,
THERESA,

08:54.181 --> 08:55.986
NOT THEIR PARENTS.

08:55.986 --> 08:59.328
YOUR JOB IS TO FEED THEM
AND KEEP THEM SAFE.

08:59.328 --> 09:00.598
LET US DO THE REST.

09:00.598 --> 09:03.070
[ SCHOOL BELL RINGS ]
OH, THAT'S MY CUE.

09:03.070 --> 09:04.608
NICE TO SEE YOU.

09:04.608 --> 09:07.615
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

09:07.615 --> 09:10.288
YEAH,
IT LOOKS REALLY BAD.

09:37.154 --> 09:39.292
[ GATE CREAKS ]

09:51.523 --> 09:53.394
[ FOOTSTEPS ECHOING ]

09:56.668 --> 09:57.671
[ THUD ]

09:57.671 --> 10:00.444
[ METAL CLANGING ]

10:03.185 --> 10:07.628
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS
IN DISTANCE ]

10:12.340 --> 10:14.345
[ DOOR CREAKING ]

10:31.120 --> 10:32.557
[ CLANG ]

10:34.662 --> 10:36.634
[ CLANG ]

10:41.646 --> 10:44.619
[ SLURPS ]

10:44.619 --> 10:47.293
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR COMING DOWN, FRANKLIN.

10:47.293 --> 10:49.498
AS THE NEW SHERIFF
IN TOWN,

10:49.498 --> 10:50.768
I'M MAKING A POINT
OF GETTING TO KNOW

10:50.768 --> 10:53.608
ALL THE SHOPKEEPERS
ON MAIN STREET.

10:53.608 --> 10:55.246
NEVER REALLY HAD

10:55.246 --> 10:58.320
A "GET TO KNOW YOU" MEETING
WITH SHERIFF POPE.

11:01.628 --> 11:06.239
FRANKLIN, WE DON'T TALK
ABOUT THE PAST HERE.

11:06.239 --> 11:08.645
YOU KNOW THAT.

11:08.645 --> 11:11.619
[ GROANS ]
LIGHTEN UP, FRANKLIN.

11:11.619 --> 11:13.557
I'M JUST MESSING
WITH YOU.

11:13.557 --> 11:15.195
OH.
[ LAUGHS WEAKLY ]

11:15.195 --> 11:18.335
BUT, LISTEN, I DID HAVE
SOMETHING OF A PERSONAL NATURE

11:18.335 --> 11:20.742
THAT I'D LIKE TO DISCUSS
WITH YOU.

11:22.847 --> 11:24.450
GOPHERS.

11:26.422 --> 11:28.727
GOPHERS?
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

11:28.727 --> 11:31.602
THEY'RE DESTROYING
MY LAWN.

11:31.602 --> 11:33.740
AND I REMEMBER LOOKING
THROUGH YOUR FILE ONE DAY

11:33.740 --> 11:35.678
AND IT SAID THAT
YOU WORKED IN, UH...

11:35.678 --> 11:38.719
EXPLOSIVE DEMOLITION.

11:40.389 --> 11:41.927
HMM.

11:44.299 --> 11:48.844
AFRAID I C-CAN'T HELP YOU,
SHERIFF.

11:48.844 --> 11:50.714
YEAH,
I SHOULD REALLY BE

11:50.714 --> 11:52.519
GETTING BACK
TO THE SHOP.

11:52.519 --> 11:54.524
SO...

11:58.266 --> 12:02.945
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

12:15.643 --> 12:17.380
Megan:
OPEN YOUR BOOKS TO PAGE 17.

12:19.252 --> 12:20.655
[ LIGHT LAUGHTER ]

12:20.655 --> 12:23.629
GO AHEAD AND LOOK
AT ALL THE PICTURES.

12:23.629 --> 12:25.567
[ LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

12:25.567 --> 12:28.307
GIGGLE IF YOU WANT.

12:28.307 --> 12:29.844
FOR OBVIOUS REASONS,

12:29.844 --> 12:34.055
YOUR TEXTBOOKS
WILL REMAIN HERE IN CLASS.

12:34.055 --> 12:39.067
PARENTS TEND TO BE UNCOMFORTABLE
WITH THESE SORTS OF IMAGES.

12:39.067 --> 12:43.077
EVEN BIOLOGY CAN BE
MISUNDERSTOOD.

12:43.077 --> 12:45.549
THE POINT IS,

12:45.549 --> 12:52.534
PROCREATION IS
A BEAUTIFUL AND BLESSED THING.

12:52.534 --> 12:54.538
AND HERE IN WAYWARD PINES,

12:54.538 --> 13:01.789
THAT REALLY IS
YOUR MOST IMPORTANT JOB.

13:01.789 --> 13:04.696
BEN, AMY.

13:04.696 --> 13:07.403
WOULD YOU STEP UP FRONT,
PLEASE?

13:07.403 --> 13:09.675
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:09.675 --> 13:11.948
COME ON, QUICKLY.

13:14.721 --> 13:20.736
AHH. BEHOLD,
THE MALE AND THE FEMALE.

13:20.736 --> 13:24.110
TWO BODIES,
BEAUTIFULLY DESIGNED

13:24.110 --> 13:30.125
TO FIT TOGETHER
EFFORTLESSLY, SEAMLESSLY.

13:30.125 --> 13:34.770
TWO PERFECT PUZZLE PIECES,
LIKE HAND IN GLOVE.

13:34.770 --> 13:36.140
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:36.140 --> 13:38.914
YES, YES, IT'S EMBARRASSING
TO TALK ABOUT.

13:38.914 --> 13:40.885
BUT WHAT IF --

13:40.885 --> 13:44.795
WHAT IF BEN WAS A BEE
AND AMY WAS A FLOWER?

13:44.795 --> 13:49.540
WELL, THAT WOULDN'T BE FUNNY
AT ALL, WOULD IT?

13:51.679 --> 13:56.924
WAYWARD PINES NEEDS
A NEW GENERATION.

13:56.924 --> 14:01.402
AND ONE DAY,
NOT TOO LONG FROM NOW,

14:01.402 --> 14:07.484
YOU ALL WILL HAVE THE HONOR OF
PARENTING THE FIRST GENERATION

14:07.484 --> 14:13.465
OF 100% ORIGINALS.

14:13.465 --> 14:15.036
NOW, TAKE A LOOK
AROUND THE ROOM.

14:15.036 --> 14:16.640
[ ALL MURMURING ]

14:16.640 --> 14:19.045
THIS IS A SMALL TOWN.
[ Laughing ] RIGHT?

14:19.045 --> 14:23.757
CHANCES ARE, YOUR MATE --
YOUR CO-PARENT

14:23.757 --> 14:26.163
[ LAUGHTER ]
IS SITTING RIGHT HERE
IN THIS ROOM.

14:26.163 --> 14:30.005
AND IT'S PART OF MY JOB
AS YOUR TEACHER AND COUNSELOR

14:30.005 --> 14:33.480
TO HELP YOU
FIND EACH OTHER.

14:33.480 --> 14:35.787
[ LAUGHS ]

14:35.787 --> 14:38.627
YOU TWO MAY SIT DOWN.

14:38.627 --> 14:41.500
[ LIGHT LAUGHTER, MURMURING ]

14:44.775 --> 14:46.780
[ SIGHS ]

14:48.852 --> 14:51.258
THAT WAS WEIRD.

14:54.566 --> 14:56.571
[ WHISTLING "TWINKLE, TWINKLE,
LITTLE STAR" ]

15:01.149 --> 15:02.853
AH, THERE YOU ARE!

15:02.853 --> 15:04.156
NURSE,
COULD YOU GIVE ME

15:04.156 --> 15:06.028
A MOMENT ALONE
WITH DR. JENKINS, PLEASE?

15:06.028 --> 15:07.030
THANK YOU.

15:07.030 --> 15:10.505
WONDERFUL NEWS.

15:10.505 --> 15:13.880
YOU KNOW, I'M DOING MY ANNUAL
FERTILITY CONSULTS THIS MORNING.

15:13.880 --> 15:18.158
AND ALREADY,
TWO NEW PREGNANCIES.

15:18.158 --> 15:21.165
IMAGINE.

15:21.165 --> 15:25.710
TWO NEW MEMBERS
OF OUR FIRST GENERATION.

15:25.710 --> 15:29.218
THAT IS WONDERFUL.

15:29.218 --> 15:33.160
DAVID, WHAT IS IT?

15:33.160 --> 15:37.605
WHY ARE THEY
TRYING TO UNDERMINE US?

15:37.605 --> 15:38.808
IS IT INEVITABLE,

15:38.808 --> 15:41.548
THIS...PASSION
FOR SELF-DESTRUCTION?

15:41.548 --> 15:43.285
HAVE YOU EATEN TODAY?

15:43.285 --> 15:47.596
PAM...
IS IT HAPPENING AGAIN?

15:47.596 --> 15:50.269
YOU ALWAYS
GET LIKE THIS.

15:50.269 --> 15:53.009
YOU WORRY SO,
AND YOU FORGET TO EAT.

15:53.009 --> 15:55.014
THEN ONCE
YOUR BLOOD SUGAR DROPS,

15:55.014 --> 15:58.757
THE WHOLE WORLD
LOOKS GLOOMY, HMM?

15:58.757 --> 16:03.636
ETHAN BURKE WILL FERRET OUT
THESE TROUBLEMAKERS.

16:03.636 --> 16:07.178
SHERIFF BURKE
WILL GET US THROUGH

16:07.178 --> 16:10.719
THIS PRESENT DIFFICULTY.

16:10.719 --> 16:12.591
THAT'S VERY GENEROUS
OF YOU.

16:12.591 --> 16:14.729
OH,
YOU BELIEVE IN HIM.

16:14.729 --> 16:17.870
I BELIEVE IN HIM.

16:17.870 --> 16:21.045
DR. JENKINS?
WAYNE JOHNSON IS HERE.

16:21.045 --> 16:23.050
OH.
THANK YOU, NURSE.

16:23.050 --> 16:26.057
BACK TO WORK.

16:26.057 --> 16:28.396
GREAT NEWS
ABOUT THE PREGNANCIES.

16:28.396 --> 16:30.869
OH, INDEED.

16:52.355 --> 16:54.092
Just be careful.

16:54.092 --> 16:56.231
ALL RIGHT, GREAT.
OKAY.

16:56.231 --> 16:58.704
FOR SURE.
YEAH. BYE-BYE.

17:01.244 --> 17:03.349
MORNING, ETHAN.

17:03.349 --> 17:05.754
FRIEND OF YOURS?

17:05.754 --> 17:07.291
OH, FRANKLIN?

17:07.291 --> 17:09.296
YEAH. I MEAN,
YOU KNOW, IT'S A SMALL TOWN.

17:09.296 --> 17:12.103
YEAH, YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN
SEEING A LOT OF EACH OTHER.

17:12.103 --> 17:14.978
I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO COME WITH ME

17:14.978 --> 17:17.951
SO WE CAN TALK MORE --
PRIVATELY.

17:17.951 --> 17:20.056
SURE, WHAT ABOUT?

17:20.056 --> 17:22.997
ABOUT THE DAMN BOMB
IN MY TRUCK, HAROLD.

17:24.768 --> 17:27.308
I-I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS.

17:27.308 --> 17:29.913
OKAY.

17:29.913 --> 17:31.350
WELL,
LET'S GO TO MY OFFICE,

17:31.350 --> 17:33.790
AND YOU CAN TELL ME ABOUT
WHAT YOU DON'T KNOW.

17:42.879 --> 17:45.419
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

17:45.419 --> 17:46.889
[ GRUNTS ]

17:50.130 --> 17:51.266
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

17:54.474 --> 17:57.114
DON'T MAKE ME SUBDUE YOU
AGAIN, HAROLD.

17:57.114 --> 17:59.386
NEXT TIME,
I WON'T BE SO GENTLE.

17:59.386 --> 18:02.861
IT'S OKAY, FOLKS.
HE TRIPPED AND FELL.

18:02.861 --> 18:03.997
LET'S GO.

18:14.323 --> 18:16.963
FRANKLIN MADE THE BOMB,

18:16.963 --> 18:19.836
AND YOU OR SOMEBODY
WHO WORKS FOR YOU

18:19.836 --> 18:21.373
PLANTED IT
IN MY TRUCK.

18:21.373 --> 18:24.046
I SWEAR, I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT A BOMB IN YOUR TRUCK.

18:24.046 --> 18:27.054
BUT YOU KNOW ABOUT THE OTHER
BOMBS THAT FRANKLIN MADE --

18:27.054 --> 18:29.460
THE ONES THAT ARE
STILL OUT THERE.

18:29.460 --> 18:32.066
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT THIS IS
ALL ABOUT, ISN'T IT?

18:32.066 --> 18:35.575
YOU WANT TO TAKE DOWN
THE FENCE.

18:35.575 --> 18:38.315
DON'T YOU
WANT TO GET OUT?

18:38.315 --> 18:41.924
JUST GO SOMEWHERE,
ANYWHERE?

18:41.924 --> 18:45.466
THERE IS NO SOMEWHERE,
NO ANYWHERE.

18:45.466 --> 18:48.340
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
I WANT NAMES...

18:48.340 --> 18:49.509
[ PEN CLICKS ]

18:49.509 --> 18:51.614
...OF EVERYBODY
IN YOUR GROUP,

18:51.614 --> 18:54.087
STARTING
WITH YOUR LEADER.

18:54.087 --> 18:56.326
WHO IS HE?

18:56.326 --> 18:59.266
OR MAYBE IT'S A SHE.

19:07.587 --> 19:09.926
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE.

19:09.926 --> 19:12.198
REALLY?
I ACTED ALONE.

19:12.198 --> 19:14.905
YOU ACTED ALONE?
MM-HMM.

19:14.905 --> 19:16.108
SO THAT MEANS THAT

19:16.108 --> 19:17.879
YOU <i>DID</i> PLANT THE BOMB
IN MY TRUCK,

19:17.879 --> 19:20.151
AND YOU WERE LYING ABOUT IT
WHEN YOU DENIED IT,

19:20.151 --> 19:23.158
BUT YOU'RE TELLING ME
THE TRUTH NOW, IS THAT IT?

19:23.158 --> 19:25.431
GREAT.

19:25.431 --> 19:28.973
[ SIGHS ]

19:28.973 --> 19:31.478
[ PEN SCRATCHING ]

19:35.589 --> 19:38.597
OKAY.

19:38.597 --> 19:40.935
GIVE THIS TO KATE.

19:40.935 --> 19:42.940
YOU CAN GO NOW.

19:45.279 --> 19:47.452
UM, I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I CONFESSED.

19:47.452 --> 19:50.192
YEAH, I GOT IT.

19:50.192 --> 19:51.929
YOU CAN GO.

19:59.481 --> 20:02.622
[ SIGHS ]

20:02.622 --> 20:04.026
[ BELL JINGLES ]

20:04.026 --> 20:07.033
MORNING, BEAUTIFUL.

20:07.033 --> 20:08.704
SORRY I'M LATE.

20:08.704 --> 20:12.179
I WISH I COULD BLAME IT
ON THE TRAFFIC.

20:12.179 --> 20:14.584
BUT SOMEHOW, I DON'T THINK
THAT'LL FLY. [ LAUGHS ]

20:14.584 --> 20:16.055
GOOD MORNING.

20:16.055 --> 20:17.592
YOU SEEM LIKE
YOU'RE IN A GREAT MOOD.

20:17.592 --> 20:19.698
HEY.
CRISPY LIKE A CRACKER.

20:19.698 --> 20:22.270
I PASSED BY THAT LOT
THIS MORNING, PLOT 33?

20:22.270 --> 20:25.010
AND I THINK
I FOUND SOMETHING.

20:25.010 --> 20:26.581
THERE APPEARS TO BE
A SUBSTRUCTURE OF SOME KIND

20:26.581 --> 20:28.452
UNDERNEATH THE SOIL.

20:28.452 --> 20:30.256
IT FELT LIKE METAL.

20:30.256 --> 20:33.063
OH, WELL,
A WATER TANK, MAYBE.

20:33.063 --> 20:36.070
Y-- BUT IT'S BURIED IN
AN EMPTY LOT, BILL, THAT --

20:36.070 --> 20:38.710
[ GROANS ]
LIFE'S FULL OF MYSTERIES,

20:38.710 --> 20:41.183
ALL CHOCK-FULL
OF HEAD SCRATCHERS.

20:41.183 --> 20:43.589
I WOULDN'T THINK ABOUT IT
TOO MUCH.

20:43.589 --> 20:48.334
BESIDES, YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T
SNOOP AROUND OUT THERE.

20:48.334 --> 20:49.737
AND WHY IS THAT?

20:55.552 --> 20:58.459
THE SECRET TO
A SAFE AND HAPPY TOWN

20:58.459 --> 21:01.466
IS EVERYONE MINDING
THEIR OWN BUSINESS.

21:01.466 --> 21:05.276
PEOPLE NEED TO DO
WHAT THEY'RE SUPPOSED TO.

21:05.276 --> 21:07.381
AND NOT DO
WHAT THEY'RE NOT.

21:07.381 --> 21:09.119
RIGHT.

21:09.119 --> 21:11.424
NOW, UH, I NEED YOU TO GO DOWN
TO THE HOSPITAL A BIT

21:11.424 --> 21:13.429
AND PICK UP SOME FILES
FOR ME.

21:13.429 --> 21:17.138
IF -- IF YOU'RE NOT
TOO BUSY.

21:19.811 --> 21:21.816
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:28.666 --> 21:30.671
I GOT YOUR NOTE.

21:30.671 --> 21:33.144
I CAME
AS SOON AS I COULD.

21:33.144 --> 21:36.118
GOOD. COME ON IN.

21:36.118 --> 21:39.526
HERE, SIT DOWN.

21:39.526 --> 21:40.796
DON'T WORRY.

21:40.796 --> 21:44.070
I DISABLED
ALL THE SURVEILLANCE IN HERE.

21:44.070 --> 21:46.175
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T CARE
ABOUT THAT.

21:46.175 --> 21:48.682
IT'S NOT FOR <i>MY</i> SAFETY.

21:48.682 --> 21:50.820
COFFEE?

21:50.820 --> 21:53.862
I HEARD ABOUT THE BOMB
IN YOUR TRUCK.

21:53.862 --> 21:56.467
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE ME.
I-I DON'T KNOW WHO DID THAT.

21:56.467 --> 21:58.205
GOOD.

21:58.205 --> 22:02.215
BUT YOU CAN FIGURE OUT WHO DID,
CAN'T YOU?

22:02.215 --> 22:04.855
BECAUSE
YOU'RE THEIR LEADER.

22:04.855 --> 22:06.794
WHAT IF I WAS?

22:06.794 --> 22:09.801
COME ON, KATE!
OF COURSE YOU ARE.

22:09.801 --> 22:11.471
LOOK, HAROLD WAS
AN ACCOUNTANT.

22:11.471 --> 22:13.543
IF THERE'S ANYBODY LEADING
A RESISTANCE IN THIS TOWN,

22:13.543 --> 22:15.548
IT'S NOT HAROLD,

22:15.548 --> 22:18.789
SO WHO ELSE IS INVOLVED
IN THIS GROUP?

22:18.789 --> 22:22.498
THIS GROUP IS THE ONLY THING
THAT'S KEPT ME SANE HERE.

22:22.498 --> 22:25.373
HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN ACTIVE?

22:25.373 --> 22:28.914
IT EVOLVED OVER TIME.

22:28.914 --> 22:31.654
WE STARTED
AS SOMETHING ELSE.

22:31.654 --> 22:35.597
JUST A FEW OF US
TRYING TO CONNECT.

22:35.597 --> 22:38.337
WE'D MEET IN SECRET,

22:38.337 --> 22:40.342
JUST TO BE REAL
WITH EACH OTHER.

22:41.812 --> 22:43.550
UH...

22:43.550 --> 22:48.529
KATE HEWSON,
UM, SEATTLE.

22:48.529 --> 22:52.505
I MISS THE FERRY BOATS,
OYSTERS,

22:52.505 --> 22:55.512
HIKING BURROUGHS TRAIL.

22:55.512 --> 22:57.785
MY FRIENDS.

23:01.795 --> 23:04.802
I'M, UH -- I'M --
I'M FRANKLIN.

23:04.802 --> 23:07.809
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
UH...

23:09.747 --> 23:11.886
IT'S ALL YOU, MAN.

23:12.956 --> 23:16.731
HAROLD BALLINGER, ST. PAUL.

23:16.731 --> 23:18.469
UM...

23:18.469 --> 23:20.006
I HAVE A FIANCÉ.

23:27.625 --> 23:30.866
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T
TELL ME ANY OF THIS

23:30.866 --> 23:32.938
WHEN I FIRST GOT HERE?

23:32.938 --> 23:35.945
ETHAN, I'VE BEEN TRAPPED HERE
FOR 12 YEARS.

23:35.945 --> 23:38.818
TRY AND IMAGINE
WHAT THAT'S LIKE.

23:38.818 --> 23:40.256
AND THEN YOU SHOW UP.

23:40.256 --> 23:41.826
AND A WEEK LATER,
YOU'RE SHERIFF?

23:41.826 --> 23:44.032
ALL RIGHT, LOOK,
IT STOPS NOW.

23:44.032 --> 23:47.540
WHY WOULD I STOP TRYING TO
ESCAPE THIS PRISON?

23:47.540 --> 23:50.815
[ SIGHS ]

23:50.815 --> 23:53.922
LOOK, THE WORLD
THAT YOU AND I KNEW,

23:53.922 --> 23:57.030
THE WORLD OUTSIDE THE FENCE,
THAT NO LONGER EXISTS.

23:57.030 --> 23:59.737
IT'S NOT 2014.

23:59.737 --> 24:03.312
IT'S NOT -- IT'S NOT EVEN
THE 21st CENTURY ANYMORE.

24:03.312 --> 24:04.716
[ SCOFFS ]

24:04.716 --> 24:05.952
WHAT -- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,

24:05.952 --> 24:08.826
IT'S NOT
THE 21st CENTURY ANYMORE?

24:08.826 --> 24:11.566
[ SIGHS ]

24:16.478 --> 24:17.648
HEY.

24:17.648 --> 24:19.386
GOOD CLASS TODAY.
OH, THANKS, AMY.

24:19.386 --> 24:20.554
YEAH.

24:20.554 --> 24:22.626
YOU AND BEN LOOK SO NICE
TOGETHER.

24:22.626 --> 24:24.063
HOW IS THAT WORKING OUT?

24:24.063 --> 24:26.536
IT'S GREAT, ACTUALLY.

24:26.536 --> 24:29.678
I REALLY LIKE HIM.
LIKE, A LOT.

24:29.678 --> 24:31.081
OH, I'M SO GLAD.

24:31.081 --> 24:33.954
AS A TEACHER,
IT'S SO FULFILLING

24:33.954 --> 24:36.961
WHEN AN ASSIGNMENT
TURNS INTO SOMETHING MORE.

24:36.961 --> 24:39.868
YEAH, HE'S SWEET.
KIND OF SHY.

24:39.868 --> 24:42.475
I DON'T THINK
HE'S HAD MUCH EXPERIENCE.

24:42.475 --> 24:46.986
YOU MIGHT BE
HIS FIRST REAL GIRLFRIEND.

24:46.986 --> 24:48.724
I WAS THINKING OF

24:48.724 --> 24:53.469
MAYBE ASKING HIM OUT
LATER TONIGHT.

24:53.469 --> 24:55.741
GO SOME PLACE SECLUDED
AND ROMANTIC.

24:55.741 --> 24:57.010
MM.

24:57.010 --> 24:59.015
I JUST -- I FEEL LIKE

24:59.015 --> 25:04.028
I'M READY FOR US
TO BE MORE...INTIMATE.

25:04.028 --> 25:06.969
HE'S NOT
PRESSURING YOU?

25:06.969 --> 25:08.974
BEN?

25:08.974 --> 25:10.711
OH, GOD, NO.

25:10.711 --> 25:13.117
I JUST HOPE I DON'T
HAVE TO PRESSURE HIM.

25:13.117 --> 25:15.690
[ LAUGHS ]
I'M SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

25:15.690 --> 25:16.959
ENJOY THIS MOMENT.
[ SCHOOL BELL RINGS ]

25:16.959 --> 25:19.499
THERE'S NOTHING LIKE
BEING YOUNG AND IN LOVE.

25:26.116 --> 25:29.424
Kate: SO, LET ME
GET THIS STRAIGHT.

25:29.424 --> 25:30.693
WHOEVER'S
BEHIND ALL THIS,

25:30.693 --> 25:32.832
THE PEOPLE UP THERE
PULLING THE STRINGS,

25:32.832 --> 25:35.538
YOU WORK FOR THEM NOW?

25:37.845 --> 25:40.985
[ SIGHS ]

25:40.985 --> 25:44.728
HAND OVER WHOEVER IT WAS THAT
PLANTED THE BOMB IN MY TRUCK,

25:44.728 --> 25:46.600
SURRENDER YOUR ARMS
AND EXPLOSIVES

25:46.600 --> 25:47.802
BY TOMORROW MORNING,

25:47.802 --> 25:50.877
AND EVERYTHING
STAYS BETWEEN US.

25:50.877 --> 25:52.882
YOU CAN'T TAKE DOWN
THAT FENCE.

25:54.887 --> 25:57.627
OKAY.

26:00.467 --> 26:03.173
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
[ METAL CLANGS ]

26:03.173 --> 26:04.242
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

26:05.914 --> 26:08.921
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

26:11.561 --> 26:13.566
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

26:20.549 --> 26:21.819
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

26:21.819 --> 26:23.691
YOU WERE RIGHT.

26:23.691 --> 26:26.564
THEY GOT TO ETHAN.

26:26.564 --> 26:28.769
WE HAVE TO ADVANCE
THE TIMETABLE.

26:28.769 --> 26:31.911
HE KNOWS ABOUT US,
KNOWS ABOUT FRANKLIN.

26:31.911 --> 26:35.185
EXACTLY. WE HAVE
A VERY NARROW WINDOW.

26:35.185 --> 26:37.090
AND WE'RE NOT GONNA GET
A SECOND CHANCE.

26:37.090 --> 26:39.863
WE HAVE TO
TELL EVERYONE.

26:39.863 --> 26:42.737
WE EXECUTE TONIGHT.

26:42.737 --> 26:43.773
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

26:49.253 --> 26:51.960
BALLINGER TOYS.

26:51.960 --> 26:55.835
OH. H-HELLO, PAM.

26:55.835 --> 26:57.105
OF COURSE.

26:57.105 --> 26:59.578
UH, IT SLIPPED MY MIND
COMPLETELY.

26:59.578 --> 27:00.915
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:00.915 --> 27:03.087
WE'VE BEEN BACKLOGGED
WITH ORDERS AND --

27:03.087 --> 27:06.696
I-IS IT -- IS IT POSSIBLE
TO RESCHEDULE?

27:06.696 --> 27:08.967
OF COURSE, I-I UNDERSTAND
THE IMPORTANCE.

27:08.967 --> 27:12.577
UH, WE'LL BE RIGHT OVER.
ALL RIGHT, THEN.

27:14.782 --> 27:18.625
IT'S OUR ANNUAL
FERTILITY CONSULT.

27:18.625 --> 27:20.596
OF COURSE IT IS.

27:20.596 --> 27:24.004
THERE'S NO POINT
IN MAKING HER SUSPICIOUS.

27:27.046 --> 27:28.917
SO...

27:31.189 --> 27:33.628
WE HAVE A MARRIED COUPLE --

27:33.628 --> 27:36.770
YOUNG, FERTILE,
IN THEIR PRIME --

27:36.770 --> 27:41.180
AND YET, SOMEHOW...
NOT PREGNANT.

27:41.180 --> 27:44.790
YEAH.

27:44.790 --> 27:46.861
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.

27:46.861 --> 27:48.732
YOUR LAB WORK IS ALL GOOD.

27:48.732 --> 27:50.870
THERE'S NO PROBLEM
WITH THE SPERM COUNT.
GOOD.

27:50.870 --> 27:54.780
AND YOU.
PERIODS REGULAR?

27:55.883 --> 27:58.890
EVERYTHING IS
IN WORKING ORDER.
HMM.

28:03.702 --> 28:07.846
WELL, THANKS SO MUCH
FOR COMING IN.

28:13.426 --> 28:15.064
YOU KNOW,

28:15.064 --> 28:17.871
I'VE ALWAYS THOUGHT
SO HIGHLY OF THE TWO OF YOU,

28:17.871 --> 28:20.276
EVER SINCE
I INTRODUCED YOU.

28:20.276 --> 28:22.047
HMM.

28:22.047 --> 28:24.754
I MEAN,
WHAT A BLEND OF GENETICS.

28:24.754 --> 28:26.893
THE PERFECT WAYWARD PINES
COUPLE.

28:26.893 --> 28:29.064
HMM. DON'T LET ME DOWN.

28:29.064 --> 28:31.169
Woman:
<i>PHARMACY, PICK UP 512.</i>

28:31.169 --> 28:33.441
<i>PHARMACY, PICK UP 512.</i>

28:33.441 --> 28:36.181
HOW MUCH TIME DO YOU NEED
TO GATHER THE TEAM?

28:36.181 --> 28:38.220
WHATEVER
YOU CAN GIVE ME.

28:38.220 --> 28:39.390
AND GET WITH TED

28:39.390 --> 28:41.796
AND SET THE BACKUP PLAN
IN MOTION.

28:41.796 --> 28:43.433
WAIT.

28:43.433 --> 28:45.438
DO YOU THINK
WE NEED BOTH?

28:45.438 --> 28:48.078
WE'RE ONLY GONNA GET
ONE SHOT.

28:57.067 --> 28:58.437
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

29:02.380 --> 29:05.387
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

29:12.939 --> 29:14.209
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

29:14.209 --> 29:17.216
[ DOORS OPEN ]

29:17.216 --> 29:18.887
KATE.

29:18.887 --> 29:21.092
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

29:22.863 --> 29:25.169
I'M VERY WORRIED
ABOUT ETHAN.

29:26.238 --> 29:29.513
COME ON.
OKAY.

29:31.184 --> 29:32.486
Kate: DID HE TELL YOU
THE STORY

29:32.486 --> 29:34.291
ABOUT IT BEING 2,000 YEARS
IN THE FUTURE?

29:34.291 --> 29:35.494
HOW THE WORLD
IS DESTROYED,

29:35.494 --> 29:37.466
AND THE WE'RE
THE ONLY HUMANS LEFT?

29:37.466 --> 29:40.473
WHAT IS GOING ON?

29:40.473 --> 29:42.211
I DON'T KNOW,

29:42.211 --> 29:44.216
BUT I THINK THEY HAVE SOME WAY
OF BRAINWASHING PEOPLE

29:44.216 --> 29:46.488
UP ON THAT MOUNTAIN.

29:46.488 --> 29:47.825
NOW, I --
KATE,
THERE'S MORE.

29:47.825 --> 29:50.363
THE WEEK
AFTER I GOT HERE,

29:50.363 --> 29:52.335
I FINALLY FOUND A PHONE
THAT WORKED.

29:52.335 --> 29:54.942
I CALLED A SECURE LINE
BELONGING TO THE SERVICE,

29:54.942 --> 29:56.913
AND AGENT HASSLER
LEFT ME A MESSAGE.

29:56.913 --> 29:57.582
ADAM HASSLER?
MM-HMM.

29:57.582 --> 29:59.052
WHAT DID HE SAY?

29:59.052 --> 30:02.160
THAT I WAS ENTERING
A GOVERNMENT EXPERIMENT.

30:02.160 --> 30:04.967
THAT I SHOULD LAY LOW,
BLEND IN,

30:04.967 --> 30:07.940
AND THAT I MAY BE
SEVERELY TESTED,

30:07.940 --> 30:10.079
POSSIBLY
BY ANOTHER AGENT.

30:10.079 --> 30:11.449
YOU THINK
THAT ETHAN IS --

30:11.449 --> 30:14.189
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I CAN'T RULE IT OUT.

30:14.189 --> 30:15.927
THERESA,
YOU KNOW HASSLER.

30:15.927 --> 30:18.199
HE IS NOTHING
IF NOT A STRAIGHT SHOOTER.

30:18.199 --> 30:20.104
HOW MUCH OF THIS
HAVE YOU TOLD ETHAN?

30:20.104 --> 30:23.979
I HAVEN'T, AND I'M NOT SURE
IT'S A GOOD IDEA TO.

30:23.979 --> 30:25.517
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
IN DISTANCE ]

30:25.517 --> 30:27.856
I REALLY HAVE TO GO.

30:35.508 --> 30:37.646
YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON,
THERESA.

30:37.646 --> 30:42.358
AND I WISH WE HAD MET
UNDER DIFFERENT CIRCUMSTANCES.

30:42.358 --> 30:44.898
I'M SO SORRY.

30:48.406 --> 30:49.610
ETHAN,
WE'RE WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

30:49.610 --> 30:51.480
YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT ME?

30:51.480 --> 30:52.617
YES.

30:52.617 --> 30:54.053
[ SIGHS ]

30:54.053 --> 30:55.390
WHAT, YOU THINK THIS
IS ALL IN MY HEAD?

30:55.390 --> 30:56.660
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
[ SCOFFS ]

30:56.660 --> 31:00.002
YOU THINK, UH,
I WAS BRAINWASHED?

31:00.002 --> 31:02.675
I SAW STUFF OUT THERE, THERESA.
I'M NOT MAKING THIS UP.

31:02.675 --> 31:04.479
EVERYTHING I TOLD YOU
IS TRUE.

31:04.479 --> 31:07.019
BUT YOU'RE TELLING ME
THAT EVERYTHING IS GONE.

31:07.019 --> 31:10.160
[ SIGHS ] EXCEPT US.

31:10.160 --> 31:12.399
AND I WANT TO KEEP IT
THAT WAY.

31:12.399 --> 31:15.674
SO PLEASE, TELL ME.
WHAT ELSE DID SHE SAY?

31:15.674 --> 31:17.244
SHE TOLD ME NOT TO TELL YOU
ANYTHING,

31:17.244 --> 31:20.117
AND THEN SHE LEFT.

31:20.117 --> 31:22.389
SHE WAS VERY EMOTIONAL
WHEN SHE SAID GOODBYE,

31:22.389 --> 31:25.297
LIKE IT WAS
A PERMANENT GOODBYE.

31:27.669 --> 31:29.574
WHERE'S BEN?

31:29.574 --> 31:31.211
HE'S AT SCHOOL.

31:31.211 --> 31:34.453
OKAY,
I'M GONNA GO GET HIM.

31:34.453 --> 31:37.594
I THINK
THEY'RE PLANNING SOMETHING.

31:40.033 --> 31:42.305
HEY,
SO I WAS THINKING.

31:42.305 --> 31:43.708
HOW ABOUT LATER TONIGHT,

31:43.708 --> 31:46.683
YOU AND I SNEAK OUT
FOR A WALK IN THE WOODS?

31:46.683 --> 31:49.423
ISN'T THAT
AGAINST THE RULES?

31:49.423 --> 31:52.163
WELL, THERE ARE RULES,
AND THEN THERE ARE <i>RULES.</i>

31:52.163 --> 31:54.702
THERE'S A SWEET SPOT
I'VE BEEN MEANING TO SHOW YOU.

31:54.702 --> 31:59.313
IT'S LIKE A LITTLE MEADOW
UP IN THE TREES.

31:59.313 --> 32:01.318
HOW WILL WE GET THERE?

32:04.292 --> 32:06.698
I HAVE A PLAN.

32:06.698 --> 32:10.374
MEET ME AFTER DINNER?
CORNER OF BIRCH AND 9th?

32:10.374 --> 32:13.515
YEAH, SURE.

32:13.515 --> 32:17.157
IT WAS FUN
IN CLASS TODAY, HUH?

32:17.157 --> 32:18.461
I DON'T UNDERSTAND

32:18.461 --> 32:21.334
WHY PEOPLE GET SO NERVOUS
TALKING ABOUT BIOLOGY.

32:21.334 --> 32:23.607
YEAH, I -- YEAH,
I KNOW, RIGHT?

32:23.607 --> 32:25.511
IT'S JUST NATURE.

32:25.511 --> 32:28.385
Ethan: BEN!

32:28.385 --> 32:29.521
ONE SECOND.

32:29.521 --> 32:31.659
[ SIGHS ]

32:31.659 --> 32:33.029
WHAT?

32:33.029 --> 32:35.236
LOOK, I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO COME HOME.

32:35.236 --> 32:38.243
I'M KIND OF BUSY
RIGHT NOW.

32:38.243 --> 32:39.613
OH. HI!

32:39.613 --> 32:41.618
I'LL EXPLAIN IT TO YOU
IN THE CAR.

32:41.618 --> 32:44.090
SAY GOODBYE.
COME ON, DAD.

32:44.090 --> 32:46.329
AMY, I-I'M TERRIBLY SORRY,
BUT BEN'S GOT TO COME HOME.

32:46.329 --> 32:48.468
OKAY.
H-HE'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.

32:48.468 --> 32:50.473
GO AHEAD.
SAY GOODBYE.

32:53.747 --> 32:55.752
SORRY.
I GOT TO GO.

32:55.752 --> 32:58.458
IT'S OKAY.
MEET ME LATER.

33:01.700 --> 33:02.703
[ SIGHS ]

33:02.703 --> 33:04.173
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

33:04.173 --> 33:06.378
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

33:17.739 --> 33:19.344
I just need to know,

33:19.344 --> 33:20.714
did you put that pipe bomb
in the sheriff's truck

33:20.714 --> 33:23.152
this morning?

33:24.422 --> 33:26.127
Damn it, Ted.

33:26.127 --> 33:28.800
The last thing we need is
him breathing down our necks.

33:28.800 --> 33:30.270
We're not murderers.

33:30.270 --> 33:33.344
Why not?
They murder.

33:33.344 --> 33:35.784
You've been to
your share of reckonings.

33:40.696 --> 33:43.703
Do you want me to do this
or not?

34:02.248 --> 34:05.390
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

34:05.390 --> 34:07.795
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

34:27.778 --> 34:30.652
NURSE PAM: Second camera
just went out at Cell 33.

34:30.652 --> 34:34.361
NO, IT'S KATE.
SHE'S TRYING TO THROW US OFF.

34:34.361 --> 34:36.366
[ ELECTRICITY BUZZING ]

34:39.641 --> 34:42.381
IN ABOUT 10 MINUTES,
THE GUARDS CIRCLE AROUND.

34:42.381 --> 34:45.254
AND ONCE THAT FENCE IS BREACHED,
THERE'S NO TURNING BACK.

34:45.254 --> 34:47.426
THEY'LL BE ON US --
FAST.

34:47.426 --> 34:51.403
[ BEEPING ]

34:51.403 --> 34:53.273
WHERE ARE
THE BLIND SPOTS?

34:53.273 --> 34:56.381
There's one at Zone 41,
right at the fence.

34:56.381 --> 34:57.585
ALMOST THERE.

34:57.585 --> 34:59.756
SO IF ANYONE'S
HAVING SECOND THOUGHTS,

34:59.756 --> 35:01.561
NOW IS THE TIME TO GO,
ALL RIGHT?

35:01.561 --> 35:02.830
OKAY, THAT'S IT.

35:02.830 --> 35:04.635
EVERYBODY STAY
RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE!

35:04.635 --> 35:06.607
DOWN ON THE GROUND!
ETHAN!

35:06.607 --> 35:08.478
I'M NOT LETTING YOU
BLOW UP THAT FENCE.

35:08.478 --> 35:11.619
GET DOWN ON THE GROUND.

35:11.619 --> 35:13.892
OKAY, FRANKLIN,

35:13.892 --> 35:15.997
DISARM THAT BOMB.

35:15.997 --> 35:19.672
DON'T DO IT.

35:19.672 --> 35:22.412
DISARM THE BOMB,
OR SHE'S DEAD.

35:22.412 --> 35:23.682
NO.

35:23.682 --> 35:26.722
[ GUN COCKS ]
NO, FRANKLIN.

35:28.059 --> 35:30.465
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

35:32.604 --> 35:34.609
[ GUN COCKS ]
NO.

35:44.566 --> 35:47.975
[ BEEPING, POWERING DOWN ]

35:50.080 --> 35:54.090
I TRUSTED YOU.
LET'S GO.

35:54.090 --> 35:59.904
COME ON, ON YOUR FEET.
LET'S GO.

36:02.878 --> 36:05.017
[ LOCK CLICKS, KEYS JINGLE ]

36:08.558 --> 36:10.563
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

36:12.902 --> 36:15.042
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

36:22.727 --> 36:24.999
WE HAD A DEAL, KATE.

36:24.999 --> 36:27.372
THEY DID SOMETHING
TO YOU, ETHAN.

36:27.372 --> 36:30.379
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW IT.
YOU'LL SEE VERY SOON.

36:30.379 --> 36:32.384
WE WILL BE BACK IN SEATTLE,
OVERLOOKING THAT BAY.

36:32.384 --> 36:36.059
SEATTLE? NO, FORGET IT, KATE.
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

36:36.059 --> 36:41.071
YOU'VE GOT TO CONVINCE THESE
PEOPLE TO STOP THIS INSANITY!

36:41.071 --> 36:42.943
IT'S NOT GONNA STOP.

36:44.714 --> 36:47.421
IT'S JUST BEGUN.

36:50.628 --> 36:52.766
WHERE'S YOUR HUSBAND?

36:55.140 --> 36:57.746
THERE'S ANOTHER BOMB.

36:57.746 --> 37:00.486
THERE'S A BACKUP.

37:00.486 --> 37:02.190
WHERE'S HAROLD, KATE?

37:04.630 --> 37:05.866
WHERE'S HAROLD?!

38:02.271 --> 38:04.276
Amy: IT SHOULD BE HERE
ANY SECOND.

38:04.276 --> 38:07.751
IT'S ALWAYS RIGHT ON TIME,
RIGHT AT 8:00.

38:07.751 --> 38:11.025
WE CAN CATCH IT
RIGHT UP TO THE PINES.

38:11.025 --> 38:12.897
UH,
WE COULD JUST WALK.

38:12.897 --> 38:14.802
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

38:14.802 --> 38:18.210
IT'S MORE FUN THIS WAY.

38:18.210 --> 38:20.817
JUST RELAX, NEWBIE.

38:20.817 --> 38:23.590
I'VE DONE THIS
PLENTY OF OTHER TIMES.

39:13.913 --> 39:16.920
[ BRAKES HISS,
ENGINE RUMBLES ]

39:22.802 --> 39:24.673
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

39:24.673 --> 39:27.079
I NEED YOU
TO LOCATE HAROLD.

39:27.079 --> 39:28.082
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

39:28.082 --> 39:30.687
[ KEYBOARD CLACKS ]

39:30.687 --> 39:34.965
HAROLD BALLINGER.

39:34.965 --> 39:39.977
LAST SEEN AT THE BIERGARTEN
LESS THAN AN HOUR AGO.

39:41.749 --> 39:43.252
WHO'S THAT?

39:43.252 --> 39:46.861
THAT'S...

39:46.861 --> 39:49.668
TED LAUFER.

39:49.668 --> 39:52.207
HE DRIVES
THE DELIVERY TRUCK.

39:52.207 --> 39:54.212
WHERE IS
THE TRUCK NOW?

39:54.212 --> 39:55.816
WELL, HE TAKES THE SAME ROUTE
EVERY DAY.

39:55.816 --> 40:00.962
FINISHES UP ON 16th,
HEADS UP MAIN TO ACCESS ONE,

40:00.962 --> 40:03.234
DROPS OFF THE TRUCK,
AND PICKS UP ANOTHER ONE.

40:03.234 --> 40:05.106
AND WHERE DOES HE SWITCH
THE TWO TRUCKS?

40:05.106 --> 40:07.345
AT THE FENCE.

40:07.345 --> 40:09.216
[ SIGHS ]

40:11.421 --> 40:12.758
WHAT'S THAT?

40:14.195 --> 40:16.166
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

40:31.002 --> 40:33.275
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

41:05.320 --> 41:08.294
[ <i>SOFT MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

41:08.294 --> 41:10.298
WHAT'S THAT?

41:51.399 --> 41:56.011
[ ENGINE REVS, TIRES SQUEAL ]

41:56.011 --> 41:58.370
HERE HE COMES.
WE GOT TO SLOW HIM DOWN.

42:05.210 --> 42:06.978
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

42:08.914 --> 42:11.583
[ GROANING ]

42:11.583 --> 42:13.151
Man: GET UP.

42:13.151 --> 42:14.886
GET UP!

42:14.886 --> 42:17.222
[ GRUNTING,
BREATHING HEAVILY ]

42:17.222 --> 42:19.624
[ ENGINE HISSING ]

42:24.496 --> 42:28.233
[ <i>SOFT MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

42:40.946 --> 42:43.081
[ BRAKES SQUEAKING ]

42:48.520 --> 42:51.356
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

42:54.125 --> 42:56.261
[ GROANING ]

42:59.531 --> 43:01.866
ARE YOU OKAY?

43:05.070 --> 43:07.205
AMY.

43:07.205 --> 43:09.341
AMY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

43:17.582 --> 43:19.584
BEN.

43:25.323 --> 43:27.993
BEN!
